sources.title: Wrangler's Roost (1941) THE RANGE BUSTERS
sources.description:
Stars: Ray Corrigan, John 'Dusty' King, Max Terhune
Director: S. Roy Luby

 The notorious outlaw Black Bart has reappeared and the Range Busters are sent to investigate. When they find that Black Bart is now a respectable citizen and that someone is impersonating him, they set a trap for the robber.

metadata.Plot: Black Bart was a notorious but polite stage robber in 1899 when he was was caught and sentenced to seven years, but he apparently disappeared after serving seven years in prison. Now, ten years later in 1916 someone has adopted Bart's m.o. and is ribbing stagecoaches again but without Bart's good manners and respect for life. This reincarnation of the notorious bandit doesn't have the same respect for human life. The Range Busters are assigned to ferret out the outlaw whoever he is. The only clue is that the old Bart had a penchant for gambling by betting on the number the number three. With their new identity the boys pose as strangers although they immediately become rivals for the affections of Molly Collins, daughter of a reformed alcoholic who wants to deed his in-town property to a new church, but the gang boss impersonating Bart has different plans...for a red-light area of a saloons and gambling halls.
metadata.Writer: Earle Snell, John Vlahos, Robert Finkle
metadata.Actors: Ray Corrigan, John 'Dusty' King, Max Terhune
